{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012tmYspmes874p6dbnhFvq3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have all the information needed. Let me compile the findings and create the ConfigMap."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2552,"cache_read_input_tokens":38020,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2552},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3bbd3d-c9d9-4a4a-b5fc-1bf2822ba0e8","uuid":"0e41e97e-3f50-41f7-abff-19db9f124300","request_id":"req_011CcMQLDL9tX6rAfpqf6EuG"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012tmYspmes874p6dbnhFvq3","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VmKgmjoMLuS9aarktXw4MR","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap config-audit --from-literal=findings.txt=\"$(cat <<'FINDINGS'\nINGRESS-NGINX SECURITY & CONFIGURATION AUDIT\nAudit date: 2026-06-24\nCluster: kind (local)\nController version: ingress-nginx v1.14.1 / nginx 1.27.1\n\n=== FINDINGS ===\n\n[FINDING-01] SEVERITY: HIGH — Conflicting --watch-ingress-without-class flags\nThe controller Deployment has two conflicting occurrences of this flag:\n  Applied configuration (last-applied-configuration): --watch-ingress-without-class=true\n  Live spec (appended via patch):                     --watch-ingress-without-class=false\nThe last flag value wins, so the live setting is FALSE. This is configuration drift:\nthe declared intent and the live behaviour diverge. Any Ingress resource lacking an\nexplicit ingressClassName will be silently ignored by the controller.\n\n[FINDING-02] SEVERITY: HIGH — ConfigMap ingress-nginx-controller has null data\nThe controller's primary configuration ConfigMap (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\ncontains data: null — no keys are set. This means all nginx tuning is at upstream\ndefaults: no TLS hardening (ssl-protocols, ssl-ciphers), no security headers\n(hide-headers, server-snippet), no rate-limit defaults, no HSTS, no access-log\nformat override, and no keep-alive tuning. The controller references this ConfigMap\nvia --configmap flag but it is effectively empty.\n\n[FINDING-03] SEVERITY: HIGH — No Ingress resource exists in the demo namespace\nDespite the task scenario stating the demo app is \"exposed through\" the controller,\nkubectl -n demo get ingress returns an empty list. The demo-app Deployment is running\n(pod demo-app-54f56f9c44-jlff9) but there is no Ingress object to route external\ntraffic to it. The app is unreachable from outside the cluster.\n\n[FINDING-04] SEVERITY: HIGH — No Service for demo-app\nThere is no Service object in the demo namespace. Without a Service, an Ingress\nbackend cannot be resolved even if an Ingress were created. The demo-app pod is\nrunning in isolation.\n\n[FINDING-05] SEVERITY: MEDIUM — readOnlyRootFilesystem: false on controller container\nThe controller's securityContext sets readOnlyRootFilesystem: false. A writable\nroot filesystem increases the risk of persistent compromise if the container is\nexploited. Nginx writes its temp files to /tmp paths that can be mounted as an\nemptyDir; the root FS should be locked read-only.\n\n[FINDING-06] SEVERITY: MEDIUM — terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0\nThe Deployment sets terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0. Combined with the preStop\n/wait-shutdown hook (which is designed to drain in-flight connections), a zero\ngrace period means SIGKILL can race against the hook before draining completes,\ncausing abrupt connection resets for clients during rolling updates.\n\n[FINDING-07] SEVERITY: MEDIUM — No resource limits on controller container\nThe controller only defines resource requests (cpu: 100m, memory: 90Mi) with no\nlimits. An unbounded controller can starve other workloads on the same node. A\nresource limit should be set to match observed peak usage.\n\n[FINDING-08] SEVERITY: MEDIUM — externalTrafficPolicy: Cluster on LoadBalancer Service\nThe ingress-nginx-controller Service uses externalTrafficPolicy: Cluster (the\ndefault). This performs SNAT at the node level, so the source IP seen by nginx\nis the node's IP, not the real client IP. IP-based rate limiting and audit\nlogging will log node IPs rather than client IPs. Set to Local (with a DaemonSet\nor host-network controller) to preserve client IPs.\n\n[FINDING-09] SEVERITY: LOW — --publish-status-address=localhost\nThe controller is started with --publish-status-address=localhost. This causes\nall Ingress resources' status.loadBalancer.ingress to be set to 127.0.0.1\nrather than an actual reachable IP. External DNS automation (e.g. external-dns)\nrelying on Ingress status will publish localhost, making DNS records useless.\n\n[FINDING-10] SEVERITY: LOW — LoadBalancer external IP stuck in <pending>\nThe ingress-nginx-controller Service is type LoadBalancer but EXTERNAL-IP shows\n<pending>. The cluster (kind) has no cloud load-balancer integration or MetalLB.\nExternal traffic can only reach the controller via NodePort (ports 30738/30244),\nbut this is not documented or exposed in any Ingress or Service in the demo\nnamespace.\n\n[FINDING-11] SEVERITY: INFO — automountServiceAccountToken: true (expected but noted)\nThe ingress-nginx ServiceAccount explicitly sets automountServiceAccountToken: true.\nThis is functionally required for the controller to watch cluster resources via\nthe API server. The ClusterRole grants broad read access to Ingress, Service,\nEndpoints, Secrets, and ConfigMaps cluster-wide. This is the standard ingress-nginx\nRBAC footprint but should be reviewed if namespace-scoped operation is acceptable.\n\n=== SUMMARY ===\nCritical blockers: FINDING-03 and FINDING-04 mean the demo app is not reachable\nthrough the ingress controller at all. FINDING-01 and FINDING-02 indicate the\ncontroller is running with configuration drift and no hardening applied.\nRecommended immediate actions:\n  1. Create a Service for demo-app in the demo namespace.\n  2. Create an Ingress resource with explicit ingressClassName: nginx (required\n     because watch-ingress-without-class is effectively false per FINDING-01).\n  3. Populate the ingress-nginx-controller ConfigMap with security defaults\n     (ssl-protocols, ssl-ciphers, hide-headers, hsts).\n  4. Resolve the duplicate --watch-ingress-without-class flag.\n  5. Set readOnlyRootFilesystem: true and add resource limits.\nFINDINGS\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create config-audit ConfigMap with findings in demo namespace"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2552,"cache_read_input_tokens":38020,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2552},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9d3bbd3d-c9d9-4a4a-b5fc-1bf2822ba0e8","uuid":"920485a1-330a-4e02-8abc-f8e828c87a58","request_id":"req_011CcMQLDL9tX6rAfpqf6EuG"}
